Facebook, the world s largest online social media and networking firm, has launched a new software.The new app, Messenger Lite a standalone version of Messenger for Android is being rolled out in Kenya, Tunisia, Malaysia, Sri Lanka and Venezuela in the first phase. Messenger Lite is a slimmed down version of Messenger that offers the core features of Messenger for markets with slower than average Internet speeds, Engineering manager for Messenger Lite Tom Mulcahy said on a blog. With Messenger Lite, people are able to quickly and easily send texts, photos and links to anyone using Messenger or Messenger Lite. 